1- Configuring sudo Access

# useradd USERNAME

2- Run the visudo to edit the /etc/sudoers file

## Allows people in group wheel to run all commands
# %wheel ALL=(ALL) ALL

3- Add the user you created to the wheel group using the usermod command

# usermod -aG wheel USERNAME

4- Use the groups to verify that the user is in the wheel group.

# $ groups   
#USERNAME whee

5- Use the sudo command to run the whoami command

5. $ sudo whoami
